This term is the creature of art, to help us up the first step of generalization. By its as- sistance we propose to reason upon all the individuals conform- ing to the law we have laid down, as safely as we can do of any one of them. There is this inconvenience attending the use of it by naturalistS, that it assumes as a fact, that which in the present state of science is in many cases a tit subjectos in- quiry; namely, that species, according to our definition‚ do exist throughout nature. It is too convenient a term to be dispensed with, even as an assumption; only care should be taken that we do not accept the abstract term for the fact.
